# This file contains a template that can be used to customize the
# configuation process performed by the `./configure' script through the
# setting of environment variables.  The commented examples below are for
# POSIX.2-compatible shells (e.g. `sh', `ksh', `bash').  Uncommented values
# given to variables in this file will override their default values.
#
# You can also customize the configuration process via the environment
# variables seen by ./configure.  For example:
#
#     For `csh'-compatible shells:
#
#	  % setenv CC cc
#	  % setenv CFLAGS -g
#	  % ./configure
#
#     For POSIX.2-compatible shells (e.g `sh', `ksh', `bash'):
#
#	  $ CC=cc CFLAGS=-g FC=gfortran ./configure
#         etc.
#
# NB: Variable assignments in this file override ones set in the environment.
#
#############################################################################
#
# C compiler:
# CC='gcc'
#
# C compiler flags:
# CFLAGS=-g
#
# C preprocessor flags:
# CPPFLAGS=-DDEBUG
#
# Fortran compiler
# FC=gfortran
# LD_FORTRAN='-static -lf2c'
#
# LDM 6.10+
# CPP_LDM=-I/usr/local/ldm/include
# LD_LDM='/home/ldm/lib/libldm.a /home/ldm/lib/libxml2.a'
#
# McIDAS package references:
# CPP_MCIDAS=-I/home/mcidas/mcidas<ver>/src
# LD_MCIDAS='-L/home/mcidas/lib -lmcidas'
#
# netCDF 4
# CPP_NETCDF='-I/home/mcidas/mcidas<ver>/netcdf/libsrc'
# LD_NETCDF='-L/home/mcidas/lib -lnetcdf'
#
# System libraries
# LD_MATH='-lm'
# LD_X11=''
#
# Installation prefix (it's best to use an absolute pathname):
# prefix=/usr/local/unidata
#
# Location for source and binary gzip-compressed tar files
# FTPDIR=/usr/local/ldm/ldm-mcidas/ftp
# FTPBINDIR=/usr/local/ldm/ldm-mcidas/ftpbin
